sections.trabecular_bone_volume:
Trabecular Bone Volume
In young rats, the lowering of plasma estrogen concentration through OVX reduced trabecular bone volume (BV/TV) by 43% compared to young intact (
Fig. 2B
). Estrogen replacement in OVX+E2 rats increased bone volume to levels similar to those in young intact rats (
Fig. 2B
). OVX in old rats had no effect on trabecular bone volume (
Fig. 3B
). However, the addition of exogenous estrogen resulted in 28% higher trabecular bone volume compared to controls (
Fig. 3B
).
